Well said!Â  Speaking for myself, Iâm happy to be labeled an antitheist.Â  Or an atheist.Â  It makes no difference to me.Â  The point is, I do not, cannot, believe, and do not wish to believe.Â  I have never envied people of faith their worldview, never esteemed the ability to consider something true without evidence, never respected as morally superior those who manage this feat of credulity and illogicality.Â  For that matter, I have never had an experience for which I sought a religious â that is, supernatural or superstitious â explanation.Â  For Aslan, though, the semantic distinction between âatheistâ and âantitheistâ is key and intended to discredit those speaking out for rationalism and against religion.
