Aslan has often argued that we atheists are eschewing interpretation and reading religious texts too literally. Â Well, if we want to see religion as the majority of believers do, we should continue to do so: three-fourths of Americans believe the Bible to be the word of God â numbers that, to the shame of the Republic, find reflection in our resolutely anti-science Congress. Â Pew research shows that a majority of Muslims believe only one interpretation of Islam is possible.Â  Chances are itâs not the Latte flavor apparently popular in todayâs university religion departments.Â  Whether or not interpretations are possible, what the religious texts actually say does matter and must be taken seriously.
